metadata.name: Morning Blooms #25
metadata.description:
"Morning Blooms" is an exploration of minimal abstract forms and colors. This is the result of my curiosity to create a complex modular system combined with calming colors.
There are several color palettes, sizes, and shapes.

Click on the artwork and press 'i' to activate interactive mode.
To save it in high quality, press 's' in the live mode.

metadata.name: Nounfall #155
metadata.description:
Nounfall is drawn exclusively from the 234 heads and 21 glasses that are used to build the current Nouns collection. The background colors are all pulled from the blessed Noun palette.

This is ok because Nouns are CC0, which basically means public domain. Check out nouns.wtf for more info.

They make for fun social media banners when cropped, if you wanna show off you fandom of Nouns.

C : Clear screen and start animation over
S : Save current image
1 -> 6 : Set pixel density to the respective number

So, if you want a high resolution file, tap `6` for it to redraw, and then `S` to save. You can also save while it's animating if you like, which is fun too.

metadata.name: rememberance #78
metadata.description:
A field of slit-scan flowers, created from slicing images from my "abstracted expressions" acrylic painting/collage series, minted on exchange.art ( https://exchange.art/series/abstracted%20expression/nfts ). I have been looking for a way to bridge my code-based art on Tezos with my physical art on Solana, and this is an attempt to do so. 

The 9 paintings used in the piece are all acrylic, charcoal, wax pastel, and collage on paper, scanned at 600dpi. The FxHash mint is coded in p5.js

metadata.name: One Day #72
metadata.description:
One day I will have the peace, the happiness of being able to live quietly, with comfort in peace, nature, and technology side by side. The fresh air and the fast download, the sound of birds and my GPU, a nice sofa, and the calm, cool breeze on my face nourish me to the point of forgetting all my problems. One day... One day all this will be true and only peace will be my gift.

___________________________________________________

|| By pressing S in live mode you can save a image

___________________________________________________

|| Mushrooms have 15%
|| Flowers have 25%

If you are lucky, you can get both
___________________________________________________

Artwork made with p5.js, p5.grain, and much love.

metadata.name: Maru #59
metadata.description:
Maru means “circle” in Japanese, it also represents many other things like integrity, infinity and the universe. The art generated through my exploration with circles felt like it needed this name.

Best viewed in full screen, Press s in live mode for a 1414x2000 download

Download a higher resolution by adding to the URL:
&density=2 / &density=3 / &density=4

Lammetje Oktober 2022

metadata.name: The Restoration Scheme: Shape Observation #41
metadata.description:
“Shape Observation” is the first episode of “The Restoration Scheme” Series. The work was based on Staghorn Coral. 

Living on the land, we have few opportunities to see corals in real life.
Most of my impressions of corals come from photos and illustrations.
So I think the first person who discovers coral must be stunned by its shape and color.
They may paint hundreds of pictures like this.

——

“The Restoration Scheme” Series

It’s a virtual action extended from the coral restoration plan led by Delta Electronics Foundation from Taiwan, consisting of five generative corals. Each of them was based on five different species of coral as the theme.

If collectors mint virtual corals, Delta Electronics Foundation will drop coral seedlings collectively in the sea. 

The project is powered by FAB DAO (Formosa Art Bank). The split will donate to the local organization from Taiwan dedicated to the coral restoration scheme.

——

About Delta 

Climate change is causing irreversible impacts. Coral reefs, known for their rich biodiversity and the capability to nourish a quarter of marine life, are at the forefront of the crisis. 

Also known as "tropical rainforests" in the sea, coral reefs have experienced five mass bleaching events in the past five years. Once global warming exceeds the 2˚C thresholds, it's likely that 99% of coral reefs will die off worldwide.

In addition to launching a coral restoration initiative along the northeast coast of Taiwan, Delta Electronics Foundation collaborates with Asia University to host "Earth Pulsing: Nurturing Life Exhibition" and releases the first art NFT featuring coral restoration. Through these actions, we hope to evoke public awareness of ecological issues. 

For more information, please visit https://delta50.deltaww.com/initiative/sea.html

——

Features
Iterations: 1 ~ 4
Tail: round, sharp
Feathering: yes, no
Color yes, no
Paper: normal, colored, white
Weight: regular, thin, bold
Special: -
Growth Speed: regular, slow, super slow

double click or press 's' to save as an image

made with p5.js

____________________________

《形狀觀察》為《恢復方案》系列第一作，品種為鹿角軸孔珊瑚。

在陸地上生活的我們其實能實際見到珊瑚的機會不多，我想起珊瑚的印象，最多是來自照片與畫。
於是想起了第一個發現珊瑚的人，一定會為他的形狀與顏色感到驚嘆不已。
所以我想像，他也許曾經畫下上百張類似這樣的畫面。

——

《恢復方案》
恢復方案是虛擬演算珊瑚實驗，一系列共五件的生成珊瑚作品，每一件對應到特定珊瑚物種。本實驗與台達電子文教基金會合作，藏家每收藏一件 NFT，台達電子文教基金會就會實際在海中植下一株對應的珊瑚苗。

這項專案與 FAB DAO （福爾摩沙藝術銀行）支援鑄造，部分分潤將直接捐助給台灣在地珊瑚保育組織，詳細資訊將於 FAB DAO Twitter 公佈。

——

關於台達電子文教基金會

氣候變遷引發許多不可逆的環境衝擊，以豐富生物多樣性著稱、滋養四分之一海洋生物的珊瑚，便是首當其衝的受害者。

被譽為「海中熱帶雨林」的珊瑚生態系，已在最近五年遭遇三次大白化，一旦升溫跨越攝氏2℃，屆時恐有多達99％的珊瑚瀕臨滅絕。

近年在東北角投入珊瑚復育的台達電子文教基金會，今年與亞洲大學共同策畫「地球˙脈動中」生態與藝術特展，並合作發行全台首見的珊瑚生成藝術NFT，喚起社會大眾對生態議題的重視。

更多資訊可參考: https://delta50.deltaww.com/initiative/sea.html

metadata.name: Hayata! #3
metadata.description:
Hayata! emerged from my brief research on one-dimensional cellular automata (CA) and developed into a full project, since the resulting patterns were much more interesting than I had expected, especially when you mix the rules together.
Since the rules of this CA are so simple, they have something ancient, original and mysterious about them, like the I-Ching or other oracle methods. So I tried to give the CA a worthy frame by making the texture look aged and handmade.
I hope that your oracle only predicts good things for you :)
------
F.D. Berlin, October '22

Size: Between 1600px and 3200px both height and width.
Libraries used: chroma.js

metadata.name: Obliques #83
metadata.description:
Obliques are a reinterpretation of Parallels, a collection of AI generated color fields by Marc Maurer. Many of the pieces in that collection are CC0, which basically means they can be reused for other projects, like this one.

Obliques takes artifacts from Parallels and uses them as brushes, painting slices of the original image on the canvas in a (hopefully) pleasant, chaotic way.

About 10% will be "Glitched".

The "Source Material" property will tell you the name of piece that it is using.

You can see Marc Maurer's Parallels project here:
https://objkt.com/collection/KT1TiSEcASGD19SW8bmqrqgSgCBkwXqDdTJ1

Obliques are also CC0, so feel free use anything here in other projects.

You can read more about CC0 here:
https://creativecommons.org/share-your-work/public-domain/cc0/

G : Toggle Grain
M : Toggle Matte
S : Save Image
1 -> 6 : Set pixel density
(Default pixel density is 1 @ 2000x2000)

metadata.name: September #77
metadata.description:
The Summer Ends
---------------
Controls:
S or double tap (mobile): Download image

A: Toggle loading animation (off by default to improve performance)

1-6: Modify scale (1 = default, 1500 x 2000px, 6 = maximum, 9000 x 12000px (performance intensive, will take a long time to render))
F: Fit to current screen size

T: Toggle grain and texture overlay
H: Toggle shape outlines

B: Cycle border sizes (0 -> 50 -> 75 -> 100 -> 150px)
C: Cycle border colors

I: Cycle visible layers

L: Toggle “live mode”. This mode will continuously redraw a new output every few seconds using the same base parameters as the original output, but with slight variations.

You can modify the x and y url parameters to set a custom size. Note that the image will change to fit the new size, but overall drawing style, colors, etc. will remain the same.
(For example, for a 1000x2000 image, add &x=1000&y=2000)
---------------
teaboswell 2022
CC BY-NC-ND 4.0, See bundle.js.LICENSE.txt for third party license information
10% of primary sales will be donated to Girls Who Code (https://girlswhocode.com)
